10. Reverse Three-Digit Number
# Reverse three-digit number

num = int(input("Enter a three-digit number: "))

digit1 = num // 100
digit2 = (num // 10) % 10
digit3 = num % 10

reverse = (digit3 * 100) + (digit2 * 10) + digit1

print("Reversed Number =", reverse)
Example Execution
Enter a three-digit number: 123

Reversed Number = 321
